	   <tr><td colspan=2>Heh--Those were just a few ideas off the top of my head bud.&nbsp;&nbsp;=).  <br><br>All I'm saying is that SKs, whether it be mostly HP related, AC cap, whatever, cannot tank nearly as good as a WAR can, and, to me at least, think that is very wrong.  SKs (&amp; PLD) SHOULD be able to tank (PLEASE NOTE THIS...), not necessarily as well as, but much closer to WAR than is currently achievable.<br><br>I'm not saying that what I suggested was the way to go--only that it was an option, clearly amongst a plethora of options.<br><br>To clarify, what I was suggesting was a few changes to the SK class.  However, all changes must be done to keep the class &quot;equal&quot; to all the other classes.<br><br>Hence, take away SK weapon damage capability, yet offset that will much better tanking ability, combined with better spells (to increase damage output), and that wouuld be fine.  The avenues to achieve that, be it higher HP, much higher AC cap--whatever, is immaterial to me.  My only point is that it SHOULD BE DONE.<br><br>It shouldnt take a great player to make an SK tank good, while an average player could make a WAR tank good; that suggests that either 1) the classes are not in balance or 2) SKs tanking ablity is far below what it should be (which is probably the current status)<br><br>SKs, at least at the moment, are generally viewed as just another melee, which really doesn't do anything critical to a group.  As a result, they are not the first class sought after for groups.  I dont know about you, but that is a frustrating element to me.  <br><br>And before anyone gets any wise ideas, I can, as Im sure many others on this board can, play my SK at a very high level, so taht isnt an issue   =)<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
