	   <tr><td colspan=2>I could careless about tanking Vindi, if I wanted to tank Vindi I would have been a warrior. I play Sk/Ranger for the fun of having spells and being able to solo when I don't feel like grouping or I wanna make some coin.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not all of us think the Sk needs to tank Vindi to be complete. As I have stated before I have been tanking with my ranger and my sk with lesser AC gear has better AC than my ranger unbuffed. The excuse that we can't tank doesn't fly with me. I know some zones need tanks with better AC and defense but I am sure they don't need to have a warrior. <br><br>I was in frenzy in Velks for 4 hours and we had 57 sk tanking for 1 hour then 55 warrior took over when sk left and guess what we had to stop pulling for a min to let cleric get mana. The difference was that the Sk could life tap.<br><br>Do I think Sk's need some work, sure but nerfing our damage output is not the way to go just to get more hps. I think actually raising our damage output would be of more benefit and keeping our hps where they are. You might as well face the fact the warrior will never be replaced as the MA on boss mobs, Verant will never make a change that would allow us to move ahead of them.  We would be better off getting stuff to make us more efficient killers in PvE. <br><br>Give us better reuse time on Leechcurse (a big cry for this is being made on sk boards). Consolidate some of our debuffs into one spell so we don't have to mem an AC tap, ATT tap and Str tap leaving our slots open for proc spells, DoTs and DD. Give us a resist debuff so when we cast it gives us agro and lets rest of group land spells. Give us higher offense not too much but a small upgrade would help with our melee output. Make HT a percentage of total hps for the mob for damage rather than a hard number.<br><br>I don't think my ideas are any better than yours but deep down inside you know that you won't get your hps and weapon nerfage. Sk's will have to make a name for themselves just as Ranger's had to post Kunark and pre Luclin. I don't expect much change after PoP comes out due to them working on EQ2. I think they may make small changes but nothing that will upset the status quo till their next money maker comes out. At which time it won't matter much if Sk's will be able to tank Vindi.<br>&nbsp;<br>Cannis 51st Ranger<br>Razer 50th Sk<br>Jeetkundo 20th Monk<br>Mikaraz 30th Warrior<br></td></tr>
